    <project_license>GPL-3.0</project_license>

    <developer_name>Brad Harding</developer_name>
    <update_contact>hugo.locurcio@hugo.pro</update_contact>

    <url type="homepage">https://www.doomretro.com/</url>
    <url type="bugtracker">https://github.com/bradharding/doomretro</url>
    <url type="help">https://github.com/bradharding/doomretro/wiki</url>

    <launchable type="desktop-id">com.doomretro.DOOM-Retro.desktop</launchable>

    <description>
        <p>
          DOOM Retro is the classic, refined DOOM source port. It is
          intentionally minimalistic in its approach, and does a few things
          differently if compared with other modern DOOM source ports. See the
          DOOM Retro wiki for details.
        </p>

        <p>
          Commercial data files from Doom 1 or Doom 2 are required to run the supported games.
        </p>

        <p>
          With Flatpak, all file-access is restricted to ~/.var/app/com.doomretro.DOOM-Retro/.config/doomretro for privacy reasons. You'll have to manually place your IWADs and PWADS there, or you should use an application like Flatseal to give Doom Retro additional permissions.
        </p>
    </description>

